    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-10T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-10T21:00:00-05:00" n="912"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d912">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">859A.01/156a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Iceland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-10T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 10, 1944—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>221. The House of Representatives unanimously passed this morning a concurrent
                    Resolution expressing the congratulations of the Congress <pb facs="1005"
                        n="993" xml:id="pg_993"/> to the Althing on the establishment of the
                    Republic of Iceland. The full text of the Resolution will be telegraphed<note
                        n="17" xml:id="d912fn17">Telegram 230, June 15, <hi rend="italic"
                        >infra</hi>.</note> to you after it has been voted by the Senate.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
